{"id":1172,"date":"2021-07-21T14:44:07","date_gmt":"2021-07-21T14:44:07","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/?page_id=1172"},"modified":"2022-11-05T21:53:17","modified_gmt":"2022-11-05T21:53:17","slug":"colon-cancer-screening","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/colon-cancer-screening\/","title":{"rendered":"Colon Cancer Screening"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"1172\" class=\"elementor elementor-1172\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-237806f elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"237806f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-24d83c2\" data-id=\"24d83c2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8178bf5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8178bf5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Large Intestine: Colon Cancer Screening<\/h1>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Colonoscopy Screening<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-79e9d0e elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"79e9d0e\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-f5457f7\" data-id=\"f5457f7\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-49940f8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"49940f8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>General Colonoscopy Recommendations<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Start: <strong>Age 50<\/strong><ul><li>*Some Societies are Moving to Age 45<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Repeat: <strong>Every 10 Years<\/strong><\/li><li>Stop: Age 76-85<\/li><li>If First-Degree Relative Has Colon Cancer:<ul><li>Start: <strong>Age 40 or 10-Years Before the Age of Diagnosis<\/strong><\/li><li>Repeat: Every 5 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>American Cancer Society (ACS)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Start: Age 45<ul><li>*Previously Recommended Age 50<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Repeat: Every 10 Years<\/li><li>Stop: Age 76-85<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>US Preventative Services Task Force (USPSTF)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Start: Age 50<ul><li>*Draft Recommendation as of January 2021 will Change Starting Age to 45<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Stop: Age 76-85<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>World Gastroenterology Organization (WGO)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Average Risk:<ul><li>Start: Age 50<\/li><li>Repeat: Every 10 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>First-Degree Relative:<ul><li>Start at 40 or 10 Years Before Earliest Relative<\/li><li>Relative &lt; 60 or 2 First Degree Relatives: Every 5 Years<\/li><li>Relative &gt; 60: Every 10 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Start: Age 50<\/li><li>Repeat: Every 10 Years<\/li><li>First-Degree Relative:<ul><li>Start: Age 40 or 10 Years Before Earliest Relative<\/li><li>Repeat: Every 5 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Colonoscopy Contraindications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Recent MI<\/li><li>Pregnancy<\/li><li>Splenomegaly<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ef030ea\" data-id=\"ef030ea\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fe84e2b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"fe84e2b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7725 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Colonoscope.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Colonoscope.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Colonoscope-300x241.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Colonoscope <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ebe662d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ebe662d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-01a427b\" data-id=\"01a427b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a671c94 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a671c94\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Novel Screening Methods<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-2960372 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"2960372\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-4db8280\" data-id=\"4db8280\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bbe6cfb elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bbe6cfb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>General<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Contraindicated in High-Risk Patients<\/li><li>Follow Up Any Positives with a Colonoscopy (The Gold Standard)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Fecal Testing<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Guaiac-Based Fecal Occult Blood Test (FOBT)<\/em><ul><li>Repeat: <strong>Every Year<\/strong><\/li><li>Procedure: Guaiac Test of Stool Sample Reacts to Peroxidase Activity of Heme (Detects Blood)<ul><li>Three Stool Samples Collected at Home \u2013 DRE Samples are Not Sensitive<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Considerations: High False-Negative &amp; False-Positive Rates<ul><li>Sensitivity (One Time Use): 50-60%<ul><li>Higher Sensitivity if Repeated Every 1-2 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Majority of Positive Tests are False Causing Unnecessary Interventions<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>False Positive: Beef, Vitamin C, Iron, Cimetidine<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Fecal Immunochemical Test (FIT\/IFOBT)<\/em><ul><li>Repeat: <strong>Every Year<\/strong><\/li><li>Procedure: Tests Feces for Hgb Using Highly-Sensitive Techniques<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Multi-Targeted Stool DNA Test (Cologuard)<\/em><ul><li>Repeat: <strong>Every 3 Years<\/strong><\/li><li>Procedure: Tests Stool Samples for Molecular Markers<\/li><li>Considerations: Optimal Set of Molecular Markers Not Yet Determined &amp; Low Sensitivity but Higher than FIT<ul><li>Sensitivity: 52-80%<\/li><li>Specificity: 87%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>CT Colonography (Virtual Colonoscopy)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Repeat: Every 5 Years<\/li><li>Procedure: CT Done with Air Insufflation for Colonic Distention &amp; Oral Contrast to Allow Digital Subtraction of Fecal Material<\/li><li>Considerations: Satisfactory for Large Polyps but <strong>Not for Small-Medium Polyps<\/strong><ul><li>Large Polyps (\u2265 10 mm):<ul><li>Sensitivity: 93%<\/li><li>Specificity: 97%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Medium &amp; Large Polyps:<ul><li>Sensitivity: 86%<\/li><li>Specificity: 86%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>All Polyps:<ul><li>Sensitivity: 45-97%<\/li><li>Specificity: 26-97%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Flexible Sigmoidoscopy<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Repeat: <strong>Every 5 Years<\/strong><\/li><li>Considerations: Unable to View Right Colon<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-8ae832f\" data-id=\"8ae832f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e2efd7a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e2efd7a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-11161 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FIT-Testing.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FIT-Testing.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FIT-Testing-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>FIT Testing <sup>2<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ab6f5a1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ab6f5a1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-11156 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CT-Colonography.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"168\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CT-Colonography.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CT-Colonography-300x101.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>CT Colonography <sup>3<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5fb86c4 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5fb86c4\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fcbf15c\" data-id=\"fcbf15c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-825fe9f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"825fe9f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Pathology Considerations<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-200f29e elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"200f29e\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-baa6f00\" data-id=\"baa6f00\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3769b01 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3769b01\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Adenoma Repeat Testing \u2013 United States Multi-Society Task Force on Colorectal Cancer (2019)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Hyperplastic Polyps (HP):<ul><li>&lt; 10 mm: Normal Schedule<\/li><li>\u2265 10 mm: 3-5 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Tubular Adenomas:<ul><li>1-2: 7-10 Years<\/li><li>3-4: 3-5\u00a0Years <a class=\"button\" style=\"background-color: #193556; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 2px;\" href=\"#MN\">Mn<\/a><\/li><li>5-10: 3 Years<\/li><li>&gt; 10: 1 Year<\/li><li>Advanced Adenoma: Repeat 3 Years<ul><li>Advanced Characteristics:<ul><li><strong>Size \u2265 10 mm<\/strong><\/li><li>Tubulovillous or Villous Histology<\/li><li>High-Grade Dysplasia<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Sessile Serrated Polyp (SSP):<ul><li>1-2: 5-10 Years<\/li><li>3-4: 3-5 Years<\/li><li>5-10: 3 Years<\/li><li>Advanced Characteristics: Repeat 3 Years<ul><li>Size \u2265 10 mm<\/li><li>Any Dysplasia<\/li><li>Traditional Serrated Adenoma (TSA)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Resection in Piecemeal Fashion (\u2265 20 mm): 6 Months to Ensure Complete Excision<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Screening: Colonoscopy with <strong>Random Bx<\/strong><\/li><li>Start: <strong>8-10 Years After Diagnosis<\/strong><ul><li>Start Immediately If Concurrent PSC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Repeat: <strong>Every 1-3 Years<\/strong><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/ibd\/\">*See Large Intestine: Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD)<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Hereditary Nonpolyposis Colon Cancer (HNPCC\/Lynch Syndrome)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Screening: Colonoscopy<\/li><li>Start: <strong>Age 20-25<\/strong><\/li><li>Repeat: <strong>Every 1-2 Years<\/strong><\/li><li>Also Screening EGD After Age 35<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/colorectal-cancer-and-polyposis-syndromes\/\">*See Oncology: Colorectal Cancer &amp; Polyposis Syndromes<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Familial Adenomatous Polyposis (FAP)<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Screening: <strong>Flexible Sigmoidoscopy<\/strong><\/li><li>Start: <strong>Age 10-12<\/strong><\/li><li>Repeat: <strong>Every Year<\/strong><ul><li>Continue Even After Colectomy<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Also <strong>Screening EGD<\/strong> Every 2-3 Years After Age 25<ul><li>*Or Start Whenever Colon Polyps are Fist Seen \u2013 Whichever Comes First<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/colorectal-cancer-and-polyposis-syndromes\/\">*See Oncology: Colorectal Cancer &amp; Polyposis Syndromes<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Colon CA Post-Resection<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Initial:<ul><li>If Entire Colon Was Seen at Prior Colonoscopy: <strong>1 Year<\/strong><\/li><li>If Entire Colon Was <strong>Not<\/strong> Seen at Prior Colonoscopy: <strong>6 Months<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Repeat: <strong>At 3 Years<\/strong><\/li><li>Other Measures:<ul><li>CEA Every 3-6 Months for 3-5 Years<\/li><li>CT Chest\/Abdomen\/Pelvis Every Year for 3 Years<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-18d1d5d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-se